description: Both the American and English Cocker Spaniels were originally developed as a hunting dog. The coats of this breed can come in a variety of colors including black, liver, red and tan. The major differences between the English and American varieties is that the American is smaller with a shorter back plus a domed head and a shorter muzzle, while the English variety is taller with a narrower head and chest. Read all about this type of canine in our easy to read Cocker Spaniel ebook. It will provide details about the typical size, demeanor, and common health problems associated with his type of dog.
